Our time at Mandarin Oriental Palace, Luzern was absolutely incredible 🪭👘

The hotel itself was stunning, and we were fortunate enough to stay in the Panoramic Rooftop Terrace Suite, which provided us with breathtaking panoramic views of the Vierwaldstättersee and the city. Additionally, the breakfast served on our rooftop terrace was simply divine ☕️🥐

However, it wasn’t just the hotel that made our experience so memorable. Lucerne is a truly enchanting city, and we fell in love all over again with its charming streets, the iconic Chapel Bridge, and the picturesque waterfront 🦢 

Visiting during the Christmas season added an extra layer of magic, with the Christmas Market bringing festive cheer to the already beautiful surroundings 🎅🏻 We were delighted to witness the first snowflakes of the season while eating heisse Marroni - hot roasted chestnut ❄️🌰

The hotel’s Christmas decorations were also absolutely enchanting, adding an extra layer of festive cheer to our stay. The lobby was adorned with beautiful wreaths, and there were several Christmas trees throughout the property, creating a warm and inviting atmosphere 🎄With the touch of festive music it truly felt like a winter wonderland, and we couldn’t help but be filled with joy and holiday spirit every time we walked through the hotel. 

We couldn’t resist taking advantage of the hotel’s spa, which offered a tranquil and rejuvenating escape 🧖🏻‍♀️
